	</hgroup>
<article class='e-content'>
	<p>I happen to make curious discoveries, as well as I end up having interesting thoughts which I need to save before they end up forgotten or while I find the right words to reformulate them and place them in the <cite><a href='zibaldone.en.liquid' lang=it hreflang=en>Zibaldone</a></cite>.</p>
	<p>I take all of these things and I throw them here.</p>
	<h2>What is <cite>The Jam</cite>?</h2>
	<p>In the wild, things like this are generally called <q><a href=https://dev.to/jbranchaud/the-digital-garden-l10 title='The Digital Garden on DEV.to'>Digital Gardens</a></q>, or <q><cite><a lang='de' hreflang='en' href='jam/public/Zettelkasten.md' title='Zettelkasten - tommi.space'>Zettelkasten</a></cite> system</q>. In my case, it is a definitely less ambitious experiment: it is mixed, heterogeneous, juicy, and sweet. I call it <cite>The Jam</cite>.</p>
	<p>From this page, it is possible to start navigating in The Jam. There are two different ways to do this:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>by choosing a tag</li>
		<li>by opening one of the macro-notes (or <abbr title='Map Of Content'>MOC</abbr>s) below, and diving deeper and deeper in growingly branched notes.</li>
	</ul>
</article>

	<aside class='subgrid'>
		<div class='two-thirds'>
			{% render 'tags.liquid', site: site -%}
		</div>
		<div class='one-third'>
			{% render 'lang-filter.liquid', lang: lang -%}
		</div>
	</aside>

	<div class='entries-list grid'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-en' class='langFilter'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-it' class='langFilter'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-fr' class='langFilter'>
		{% for entry in collections.jam %}
			<a class='little box{% unless entry.data.main %} background{% endunless %}' href='{{ entry.url }}' hreflang='{{ entry.data.lang }}' title='{{ entry.data.title }}' {% if entry.data.main %}data-target-main{% endif %}>
				<h2>{{ entry.data.title }}</h2>
				{% if entry.data.description %}
					<p>{{ entry.data.description | markdownify | strip_html | truncatewords: 30 }}</p>
				{% endif %}
				{% render 'entry-tags.liquid', tags: entry.data.tags, site: site, size: 'tiny' %}
			</a>
		{% endfor %}
	</div>
</main>
